    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "2 Corinthians",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 6,
        "summary": "Now is the day of salvation\u2014God's ministers must walk uprightly and bear all things\u2014Saints should not be unequally yoked with unbelievers.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "We then, as workers together with him, beseech you also that ye receive not the grace of God in vain.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 3:9.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "(For he saith, I have heard thee in a time accepted, and in the day of salvation have I succoured thee: behold, now is the accepted time; behold, now is the day of salvation.)",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 49:8.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 34:32 (31\u201334).",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 150,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Giving no offence in any thing, that the ministry be not blamed:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 14:13. TG\u00a0Offense.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But in all things approving ourselves as the ministers of God, in much patience, in afflictions, in necessities, in distresses,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 11:23. TG\u00a0Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 127:2 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In stripes, in imprisonments, in tumults, in labours, in watchings, in fastings;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rioting and Reveling.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "By pureness, by knowledge, by longsuffering, by kindness, by the Holy Ghost, by love unfeigned,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purity.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kindness.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:41 (41\u201342).",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "By the word of truth, by the power of God, by the armour of righteousness on the right hand and on the left,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 13:12.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "By honour and dishonour, by evil report and good report: as deceivers, and yet true;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As unknown, and yet well known; as dying, and, behold, we live; as chastened, and not killed;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As sorrowful, yet alway rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mourning.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 8:9.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "O ye Corinthians, our mouth is open unto you, our heart is enlarged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:32 (25\u201332).",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 4
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye are not straitened in us, but ye are straitened in your own bowels.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:45.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now for a recompence in the same, (I speak as unto my children,) be ye also enlarged.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers: for what fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness? and what communion hath light with darkness?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Interfaith; Marriage, Temporal.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fellowshipping.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 3:13; Ezek. 14:3.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Light [noun].",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And what concord hath Christ with Belial? or what part hath he that believeth with an infidel?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And what agreement hath the temple of God with idols? for ye are the temple of the living God; as God hath said, I will dwell in them, and walk in them; and I will be their God, and they shall be my people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 10:21 (19\u201322).",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Body, Sanctity of; Temple.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 26:12. TG\u00a0God, Presence of.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 151
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore come out from among them, and be ye separate, saith the Lord, and touch not the unclean thing; and I will receive you,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 25:10; 53:2; 84:50 (49\u201353).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Separation.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And will be a Father unto you, and ye shall be my sons and daughters, saith the Lord Almighty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 31:9 (1, 9).",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sons and Daughters of God.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
